Third-party attributions
================================================================================

This project draws inspiration and design ideas from the following open-source
projects. Where specific code is directly adapted, the affected file includes a
header comment identifying the source and its original license. Items listed
here without a specific file reference are acknowledged as high-level design
inspirations rather than code reuse.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
aplaceforallmystuff/mcp-local-llm — MIT License
https://github.com/aplaceforallmystuff/mcp-local-llm

    Inspiration for task-semantic MCP tool naming (local_summarize,
    local_draft, local_classify, local_extract, local_transform,
    local_complete), and for exposing configuration through environment
    variables rather than hardcoded defaults.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
yayoboy/Claude-Desktop-LLM — MIT License
https://github.com/yayoboy/Claude-Desktop-LLM

    Reference for the Claude Desktop .mcpb manifest.json structure,
    user_config schema, and build-script pattern. Used when designing
    the packages/claude-desktop bundle.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
rawveg/ollama-mcp — AGPL-3.0-or-later
https://github.com/rawveg/ollama-mcp

    Referenced for integration patterns with the official `ollama` npm SDK
    (retry/backoff and error-mapping approaches). No code is copied from this
    project; only behavioral patterns are reproduced independently.

